        <t:body>
            <t:listPerson>
                <t:person sex="1">
                    <t:persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1">ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</t:persName>
                    <t:persName xml:lang="gez" type="normalized" corresp="#n1">Gabra Mikāʾel</t:persName>
                    <t:persName><t:roleName type="title" xml:lang="gez">ʾAbuna</t:roleName></t:persName>
                    <t:persName><t:roleName type="title" xml:lang="gez">ʾAbbā</t:roleName></t:persName>
                    
                    <t:persName xml:lang="ar" xml:id="n2">ميخائيل الحبشي</t:persName>
                    <t:persName xml:lang="ar" type="normalized" corresp="#n2">Mīhāʾīl al-Ḥabašī</t:persName>
                    <t:persName><t:roleName type="title" xml:lang="ar">Qummuṣ</t:roleName></t:persName>
                    
                    <t:occupation type="ecclesiastic">monk, owner</t:occupation>
                    
                    <t:residence>He is associated with <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0354DB">Dabra Bizan</t:placeName> and
                        <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0352EA">ʾƎndā ʾAbbonā</t:placeName> in the manuscripts attesting him.</t:residence>
                    <t:floruit notBefore="1875" notAfter="1960"/>
                    <t:note>
                        <t:p>A monk and consecrated priest who resided in
                            <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0478DS">Dayr as-Suryān</t:placeName> in the
                            19th or early 20th century.</t:p>
                        <t:p>The modern Arabic manuscript description placed on a paper sheet inside <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop13">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 13</t:ref> states
                        that Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī was born in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1178AddiNa">ʿAddi Näfas</t:placeName> in Eritrea and that his mother's name was
                        <t:foreign xml:lang="ar">Lītā Māryām</t:foreign>, possibly a transcription of <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Walatta Māryām</t:foreign>.
                            In <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop9">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 9</t:ref>, the name of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12967WalattaM">Walatta Māryām</t:persName> was erased
                            and substituted with that of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12002Gabrami">Gabra Mikāʾel</t:persName>. There is no indication in the manuscript as to whether both
                        persons were related. On the basis of the 
                      data from <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop9">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 9</t:ref> one can assume that <t:foreign xml:lang="ar">Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī</t:foreign>
                    is an Arabic adaptation of the name <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Gabra Mikāʾel</t:foreign>.</t:p>

                      <t:p>  The <t:ref target="https://stmaryrodelfarag.com/%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82%D9%8A%D9%86/">website of the
                            church St Mary in Rawḍ al-Farag in Cairo</t:ref> states that a <t:foreign xml:lang="ar">qummuṣ</t:foreign> Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī lived in
                          this church, until
                          <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3260CyrilVI">Cyril VI</t:persName> ordered all monks to return to their monasteries. This decree was issued by Cyril VI in 1960,
                          <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/GT9Q7HFI"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:OMahony2007Tradition"/><title level="a">Tradition at the heart of renewal: the coptic
orthodox church and monasticism in modern
Egypt</title><title level="j">International Journal for the Study of the Christian
Church</title><author><t:forename>Anthony</t:forename><t:surname>O'Mahony</t:surname></author><date>2007</date><biblScope unit="volume">7</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">3</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">164-178</biblScope><t:citedRange unit="page">171</t:citedRange></t:bibl>.
                          Since it was impossible for him to return to his native country, he went to <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0478DS">Dayr as-Suryān</t:placeName>,
                          were he died.  Whether this person is identical with the Gabra Mikāʾel/Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī mentioned in the manuscripts of
                        <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0478DS">Dayr as-Suryān</t:placeName> can only be speculated.</t:p>

                       <t:p> It cannot be excluded that Gabra Mikāʾel mentioned in the manuscripts <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop9">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 9</t:ref>,
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop10">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 10</t:ref> and <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop13">Egypt, Dayr as-Suryān, DS Ethiop. 13</t:ref> might refer to more than one person.</t:p>
                    </t:note>
                </t:person>
                
            </t:listPerson>
